fspress is a little program that helps you develop and compile a blog from
markdown files in your file system.


Installation and basic usage:
  $ go get github.com/minond/fspress    # installs fspress and fspressc
  $ fspress                             # start the server with default settings
  $ fspressc                            # geneate files using default settings


Usage of fspress:
  -autoreload
        auto reload posts on an interval. requires dev mode
  -dev
        run blog in development mode
  -glob string
        directories to check for post files (default "[0-9]*.md")
  -listen string
        host and port to listen on (default ":8081")
  -post-template string
        path to post template file (default "post.tmpl")


Usage of fspressc:
  -glob string
        directories to check for post files (default "[0-9]*.md")
  -out string
        output directory (default ".")
  -post-template string
        path to post template file (default "post.tmpl")
